eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 10 Years
Maximum age: 80 Years
This trial does not accept healthy volunteers.

At least 21 days must have elapsed since the completion of the last dose of
             VEGF-Trap, and at least 7 days since a VEGF blocking tyrosine kinase inhibitor.
             Subjects must have recovered from any VEGF blocking drug-related toxicity (e.g.,
             proteinuria).

groups.description: Patients undergo proton re-irradiation daily for 3-8 weeks. Beginning 4-12 weeks after completion of radiation therapy, patients then receive pembrolizumab IV on day 1. Treatment repeats every 21 days for up to 8 courses in the absence of disease progression or unacceptable toxicity.

interventions.name: Drug, Food, Chemical or Biomedical Material

groups.name: Treatment (proton re-irradiation, pembrolizumab)

groups.description: Cryopreserved bone marrow samples are collected for in vitro treatment with increasing doses of FLT3 tyrosine kinase inhibitor TTT-3002 and analyzed for FLT3/ITD mutations, FLT3/KD mutations and wild-type FLT3 AML via MTT assay. Samples are also analyzed for FLT3 phosphorylation in FLT3/ITD and FLT3/KD patient blasts via Western blot. Xenograft models of primary human pediatric FLT3 mutant AML samples in immunocompromised mice are studied for spleen size, WBC counts, and percentage leukemic bone marrow engraftment at 6, 10, and 14 weeks following tail vein injection of 1 x 10^6 human leukemic bone marrow cells. Samples are allowed to engraft for 2 weeks followed by FLT3 tyrosine kinase inhibitor TTT-3002 treatment BID for 4 weeks and a vehicle treated cohort.
groups.name: Ancillary-Correlative (MTT assay, western blot, xenograft)

outcome_measures.analysis_method: DLT will be defined as any non-hematologic toxicity of grade 3 or greater severity (excluding asymptomatic grade 3 laboratory abnormalities that are not life-threatening and respond to treatment; grade 3 fatigue; grade 3 nausea, vomiting or diarrhea occurring without optimal prophylaxis; or expected grade 3 rituximab infusion reactions). Any grade 4 non-hematological toxicity, as well as any irreversible grade 2 cardiac, renal or neurologic toxicities, will be considered dose-limiting. Grading of non-hematologic toxicities will be according to NCI CTC version 3.0.
outcome_measures.measure: Maximum tolerated dose of obatoclax mesylate

outcome_measures.analysis_method: OS is defined as the time from first dose of study medication until death due to any cause
outcome_measures.time_frame: Primary analysis perform 20 weeks after LPFV in the 3 cohorts of primary interest
